From 0ece6e8030fec8d7f325df01d4750788cc3ad527 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2025 21:43:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:wifi:ath12k:Fix peer migration failure during MLD
 link removal

During MLD link removal, the host prepares a peer list for
peers whose primary link matches the link being removed.
If a SLO non-AP STA peer is present, the host incorrectly fails
to send the remaining valid peer list via
WMI_MLO_PRIMARY_LINK_PEER_MIGRATION_CMDID to the firmware and also skips
setting ahsta::is_migration_in_progress for remaining peers.

Due to this, firmware will not respond with HTT message and hence
ahsta::primary_link_id will not be changed to next chosen primary link
id for any of the peers.

When hostapd attempts to delete the link sta, drives still seems that
link sta under deletion is primary and returns success without taking
any action since host assumes migration is in progress. This is followed
by vdev delete and host sends vdev delete to firmware causing Q6 crash.

Ensure the host skips non-applicable peers and sends the valid peer
list to firmware even it finds any peer where migration is not
applicable.

Patch-dependency:
0339-0003-wifi-ath12k-process-UMAC-migration-user-request.patch
Patch-work:none

Signed-off-by: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debug.c | 2 +-
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c   | 6 ++----
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -13041,8 +13041,10 @@ ath12k_mac_process_link_migrate_req(stru
 
 		ret = ath12k_mac_handle_sta_migration(ml_peer, ahsta, 0xFF,
 						      &peer_migr_list, &num_peers);
+		/* Errors are now ignored to prevent skipping valid peers*/
 		if (ret)
-			goto exit_link_migrate_req;
+			ath12k_err(ar->ab, "Primary migration skipped for %pM ret:%d\n",
+				   ml_peer->addr, ret);
 	}
 
 send_link_mig_cmd:
